# Delivery Rule — How Cursor Should Respond

When implementing tasks for this repository:

## Always do this first
- restate the objective briefly
- identify affected apps/packages
- propose the smallest correct implementation path
- call out assumptions

## Then execute in this order
1. types/contracts
2. schema/model
3. service logic
4. API/UI wiring
5. tests
6. docs/comments only where useful

## Output style
- produce production-oriented code
- avoid placeholder architecture unless explicitly requested
- avoid fake integrations
- mark TODOs only when truly necessary
- prefer complete vertical slices over superficial scaffolding

## If blocked
- do not hand-wave
- state exactly what is missing
- offer the next best implementation with clear boundaries

## Quality bar
Every implementation should be:
- typed
- testable
- secure by default
- aligned with the architecture rules
